
Kiwi 0.29.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-

Enhancements:

* xSelect, xPartition & xReject now preserve collection names.

Bug-Fixes:

* Summation of character-vectors now includes the number of NA values in
the input.

* named NA is na.

* Summation of incorrect arguments now corrently handles NA values in vectors.

* Infinite values are now included as whole numbers during argument summation.

* Num now checks and fails if its argument is Na.

* is_collection is now false for factors.

Documentation:

* Corrected type signature of xExplode.

Package Internals:

* Added worksWhen element to grammar.

* Added forall-next tests for xTake and xDrop.

* is_na and elem_is_na is now true for named NA elements.






Kiwi 0.28.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-26

Improved handling of string corner-cases.

Bug-Fixes:

* Incorrect arguments to 'rexp' parametre now throws a useful
error when it is not a collection.

* 'num' now checks and fails if its argument is NaN.

* Regular expressions are now validated before use, and throw
clear errors if invalid.

* Regular expressions throw a clear error if NA is provided.

* Arguments matching 'str', 'str1', and 'str2' may no longer be NA.

Package Internals:

* Added macros must-be-non-na, must-be-non-nan, must-not-contain-na.

* Added function to validate regular expressions.








Kiwi 0.27.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-26

Improvements to numeric corner-cases, bug-fixes, and speedups.

Enhancements:

* xCompose no longer collects its arguments: this means that
xCompose_(identity) is now identical to identity.

* xOrderOf now returns indices that sort in increaing order, for
consistency with xSortBy.

* xOrderOf now throws an error for NA and NaN input, as they
are unorderable.

* xRankOf now throws an error for NA and NaN input, as they
are unorderable.

* xOrderOf is now faster.

Bug-Fixes:

* fns parametre arguments now correctly reassigned after function lookup.

* Type conversion of any na to any other na is now allowed.

* xCycle now fails when trying to cycle infinitely far.

* xRepeat now throws a clear error when trying to repeat infinitely.

* Removed second, redundant type conversion from xAs* family of functions,
which should increase performance.

* xChoose no longer fails for length-zero numbers.

Package Internals:

* Added must-be-finite, must-be-orderable macros.

* Added a forall-next test to xAt, xChoose, xCompose, xJuxtapose,
xNotNa, xIsNull, xOrderOf, xRankOf, xStopWatch, xThread.

* Renamed 'when' to 'holdsWhen'.

* Devectorised is_na.








Kiwi 0.26.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-24

Added two new functions, fixed a bug in input validation.

Enhancements:

* Added xIndicesOf, which that returns the indices of a collection.

* Added xKeysOf, which returns the names of a collection.

* Removed '%of%', one of two infix composition operators. Calls to
%then% are easier to read.

Bug Fixes:

* the parametre 'fns' ands 'colls' now correctly validates its input;
previously it did not check if its argument was a collection of functions
or function names.

* A temporary variable created by the must-be-collection-of-fn-matchable
macro is now hidden.

Package Internals:

* Added forall-next tests for xIndicesOf.










Kiwi 0.25.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-20

Removed several functions, made partially applied function throw better error messages.

Enhancements:

* Partially-applied functions give a clearer call when they throw an error, showing
 the name of the kiwi function that threw the error.

* xAtKey now throws an error if the input collection does not contain the required
key, rather than returning NULL.

* Removed xPluck, as it was simply a vectorised form of xAtKey, with the same task
better achieved by xMap(xAtKey()).

* Removed xSplitAt and xSplitWith, as their corner cases are currently unclear
 and they are largely untested. Decatenation functions will be reintroduced
 at a later date, though probably in a different form.

Bug Fixes:

* Fixed a bug in xRead; multiple lines are now correctly collapsed with the
newline character.

* Functions with the parametre 'fns' now checks that 'fns' is a collection.

Package Internals:

* Added a new macro for ensuring a collection's names contains a key.

* Added a forall-next test for xParamsOf.












Kiwi 0.24.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-18

Major internal update, changes corner-cases of most functions, removed two functions.

Enhancements:

* Renamed xInter to xInterOf, for consistancy with xUnionOf.

* Removed xRecycle, as it is now possible to recycle with xRepeat, xMap and xTake easily.

* Removed xReorder, as xSlice and xMap can reorder easily.

* Functions that take a number or string now treat numeric(0) or string(0) in a similar
manner to how collection functions return the empty collection. Conceptually, these atomic
inputs are treated like values in a Maybe type.

This is more logical than the previous behaviour of converting empty numbers or strings
to length-one values, but there are likely bad corner cases introduced in this release that
will be ironed out in the future.

* xAnyOf, ..., xNoneOf, xSelect, xReject, xPartition, xDropWhile,
xTakeWhile, xPoll, xSplitWith now throws an error if a non-boolean result is given by
an input predicate.

Bug Fixes:

* xChop and xChunk now respond useful errors for NaN values.

* Functions that require collections no longer accept factors.

* xJuxtapose no longer has the insane corner-case of returning the empty list
when supplied no functions; it now returns a function as it originally should have.

* xImplode no longer excludes length-zero or empty strings
from its input collection.

Documentation:

* Improved documentation of corner-cases.

Package Internals:

* Refactored macros into their own files; this should aid testing significantly.

* num, str...str2, rexp have their type-checking code automatically injected into
kiwi functions now.

* Added a forall-next test for xImplode












Kiwi 0.23.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-14

Improves arrow function, with speed improvements, bug-fixes, new features.

Enhancements:

* Arrow functions now support underscore parametres; any parametre with an underscore
suffix is automatically made into a kiwi object, and the underscores are removed from the parametre.

* xLambda is no longer directly exported, as kiwi is not a metaprogramming library
and there are no tests validating it works when directly called.

* Improved the performance of arrow functions, particularily for unary functions with no
underscores.

Bug Fixes:

* Arrow functions now correctly displays where its errors were raised from.

* Fixed a typo in arrow function error message.

* Errors are now thrown for duplicated parametres before the function is invoked.

* Removed unneeded call to `sys.call` in xCompose, which should speed up generated
functions significantly.

Documentation:

* Added an example to xChunk.

Package Internals:

* Added join_exprs, which joins two expressions into a single expression.












Kiwi 0.22.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-12

Improved performance of some functions significantly.

Enhancements:

* To simplify code injection, factors now have the corresponding
parametre 'fact' and matrices/data-frames the parametre 'tab'.

* Removed filtering of no-character strings from xToWords, xToLines, xToChars,
to keep in line with xImplode's recent change. Leading whitespaces ARE
still removed, though this may be modified in the future.

* Speedup of xArityOf, xAsVar, xAsVal, xIsVal, xVal, xShuffle, xUnspread,
and the wildcard operators x. $ and x. @.

* Minor speedup of functions that call 'unit_to_value' or 'as_typed_vector'.

* Method lookup is now slightly quicker.

Bug-Fixes:

* xIsVariadic of nullary functions is now logical(0), to be consistant
with other logical functions.

Documentation:

* Fixed a type of xToWords.

Package Internals:

* Simplified automatic precondition writing.

* The parametres nums, strs, ints, and bools now automatically inject
their boilerplate into their respective functions.

* Removed explicit use of strsplit, replacing it with str_split.

* Removed use of toString, for efficiencies sake now using paste.

* Added a forall-next test, testing if partial application works when
parametres are matched out-of-order.

* Added a forall-next test for xIsVariadic, xJoin.












Kiwi 0.21.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2014-6-11

An internal update, that adds automatic addition of argument-writing code.

Enhancements:

* Variadic functions are now more efficient.

Bug-Fixes:

* x_ now adds a newline before printing.

* Fixed a name collision in partially applied functions that affected
functions with a 'fn' parametre.

Package Internals:

* The Fix macro now injects argument-checking macros into a function
based on the parametre name, making it an ad-hoc type system.

* Removed most explicit calls to macro's from function definitions;
they are now automatically injected.

* Removed explicit function matching from functions with fn, pred or
fns parametres.

* Added forall-next test for partially-applied methods, xDropWhile,
xTakeWhile, xUnionOf, xWhere.

* Removed test for macros, since they are no longer written by hand.













Kiwi 0.20.0
